<chapter id=quick-start>The Desktop at a Glance
	<idx>overview of desktop<\idx>
	<idx>desktop overview<\idx>
	<idx>File Manager<\idx>
	<idx>Style Manager<\idx>
	<idx>Front Panel<\idx>
	<idx>desktop<\idx>

<newline>
To help you organize and manage your work, the desktop provides windows, 
workspaces, controls, menus, and the Front Panel.

<list bullet tight>
<item> <term nogloss>Windows<\term> contain software applications and are 
framed with controls so you can move them, size them, or place them in 
additional workspaces. 
<!-- See <xref survival-skills> and <xref ManagingWindowsSI>. -->

<item> <term nogloss>Workspaces<\term> are the screen areas where you place the 
windows needed for your work, arrange them, and put them away when you're done.  
<!-- See <xref UsingWorkspacesSI>. -->

<item> <term nogloss>Controls<\term> enable you to manipulate objects, select 
choices, or type information. 
<!-- See <xref SettingUpOrganizingWorkspacesSI>. -->

<item> <term nogloss>Menus<\term> provide access to commands you use to manage 
windows and operate applications.  
<!-- See <xref UsingMenusSI>. -->
 
<item> The <term nogloss>Front Panel<\term> is a collection of frequently used 
controls, available in every workspace.  
<!-- See <link hyperlink="FPanel _hometopic" JumpNewView>the Front Panel help 
volume<\link>. -->
<\list>
 
Here are some of the windows, icons and objects you'll encounter as 
you use the desktop: 

<p gentity=q-mini-icons gposition=left> 
<term nogloss>Window icons<\term><newline><newline>
When you <emph>minimize<\emph> a window, it becomes an icon on the 
workspace.  Shown here are the window icons for File Manager, Style Manager, 
and Text Editor.<newline>
<newline>To minimize a window, click the minimize button near the upper right 
corner of the window frame.<newline>
&empty;<graphic entity=VI-ZoomedViewOfMinimizeButton>&sigspace; Minimize button
<newline>
To restore the window, <term>double-click<\term> mouse button 1 on
the icon.<newline>

<newline>&empty;
<term nogloss>Style Manager<\term>
<p gentity=q-mini-stylemanager gposition=left><newline>&empty;

Use Style Manager to easily customize many elements of the desktop including:
<list bullet tight>
<item> Colors
<item> Workspace backdrops
<item> Font size
<item> Keyboard, mouse, and window behavior
<\list>

<p gentity=VI-StyleManagerFrontPanelControl gposition=left>To start Style 
Manager, click its Front Panel control.

&empty;<newline>

<p gentity=q-mini-desktop-icons gposition=left>
<term nogloss>Workspace objects<\term><newline><newline>
You can place the files, folders, and <term action>actions<\term> you use 
frequently on the workspace backdrop as icons.<newline>
<newline>To place an object on the workspace, <term>drag<\term> its icon from a 
File Manager or Application Manager window and drop it directly on the 
workspace backdrop.<newline>
<newline>A workspace object is a <emph>reference<\emph> to the actual object, 
not a copy.<newline>
 
<newline>&empty;
<p gentity=q-mini-filemanager gposition=left>
<term nogloss>File Manager<\term><newline><newline>
File Manager displays the files, folders, and programs on your system as 
icons.  Working with File Manager icons saves you from having to learn complex 
commands.<newline>

<p gentity=VI-FileManagerFrontPanelControl gposition=left><newline>To open a 
File Manager view of your home folder, click the File Manager control
in the Front Panel.<newline>

&empty;<newline>
<newline><term nogloss>Application Manager<\term>
<p gentity=q-mini-AppMgr gposition=left><newline>&empty;

Application Manager provides easy access to the CDE and OpenWindows applications 
and actions you use in your everyday work.<newline>
<newline>You can place the applications and actions you use frequently on 
the workspace backdrop.<newline>

<p gentity=VI-AppMgrIcon gposition=left>To open Application Manager,
click its Front Panel control.<newline>

&empty;<newline>
<newline><term nogloss>Front Panel<\term>
<p gentity=q-mini-frontpanel gposition=left><newline>&empty;

The Front Panel provides controls, applications, and indicators you use in 
your everyday work.  The Front Panel also provides the <emph>workspace 
switch<\emph> for selecting a workspace.<newline>&empty;<newline>

